Vol / Page:  144
Edition:
Quote:  The <i>battler</i> seems [in Australia] to have been the poorest itinerant. In this sense, the word is not current in New Zealand where <i>battler</i> is used for a person who puts up a hard fight against adverse conditions without giving in, and is thus a general terms of praise.
