Date:  0/0/1988
Source:  Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author:  McGILL
Vol / Page:  13
Edition:
Quote:  <i>battler</i> conscientous worker approved of by peers; reflects antipodean recognition of life's strugglers, the word also meaning a swagman; a petty punter living on winnings; a prostitute independent of ponce or brothel; eg `Bob has no flair, but he's a battler.' ANZ.
